dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c Joyce b McCarthy 76 (79b 5x4 2x6 108m) SR: 96.2

dismissalComment.html: strikes first ball, Morgan dinking to extra cover! The change works and again McCarthy gets a wicket in his first over... Like Root, Morgan was looking to get on with things, he made a bit of room but this was well bowled, a cutter giving him less pace to work with and he sliced it to the right of Joyce, who plunged forward to hold a good catch

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root c Balbirnie b Chase 73 (73b 8x4 0x6 106m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: skips out and launches the ball... straight to mid-off! Root departs trying to lift the tempo, solid connection on the shot but didn't get enough elevation and he ended up drilling it to the man on the edge of the ring

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales b Murtagh 32 (35b 6x4 0x6 46m) SR: 91.42

dismissalComment.html: bowled him, Murtagh strikes! Ireland have their wicket, and it's just reward for some forensic probing from the Middlesex old stager on his home ground... It was on a perfect length, nipping back up the slope, Hales was really in no-man's land trying to drive and the ball snaked between bat and pad to hit middle and leg. That's a bingo!

dismissalText.commentary: George Dockrell b Wood 28 (30b 2x4 1x6 56m) SR: 93.33

commentTextItems.html: all over! That's a convincing way to end things as Wood spears a pinpoint yorker through Dockrell

commentPostTextItems.html: England win by 85 runs and take this short series 2-0, as was expected. Two very efficient victories although they had to dig a little deeper at stages today. It was an improved display from Ireland with bat, ball and in the field even if a gulf still remained. England's innings was set up by Morgan and Root then finished off by Bairstow and Rashid. Ireland made a flyer with the bat before Jake Ball and Liam Plunkett slowed them, followed by Root's career-best with the ball. England's players (most of them) now head back to the Royal London Cup for a few days - Morgan and Billings back to the IPL - then they have a training camp in Spain ahead of the three-match series against South Africa. Their Champions Trophy campaign begins on June 1. For Ireland, it's back home for an important triangular series involving New Zealand and Bangladesh. A chance for more top-level cricket. Will Ireland's selectors decide to look at some new faces? I'll bring you the presentation shortly.

William Porterfield "I thought we were much improved today. We put a lot of things right. We kept going even through that big partnership. With the bat, just a couple of wickets behind the game. Lot of credit Barry McCarthy for coming in for a big game. We did a lot of hard work, not making easy for anyone to start, but credit to Bairstow and Rashid at the end. But lads put their hand up. After Friday it would have been easy to hide away, but we took a step forward. Even when we were six down."

Eoin Morgan "Today presented different challenges, cloud cover this morning and the openers did really well. We should have been more clinical, one of us should have got a big score, but Jonny and Adil led us home really well. [Jonny] is another selection headache, but it's a great position to be in. The quality of cricket coming up is extremely good and that's what we want. Great to see Woody back, getting more overs under his belt."

The Man of the Match is Joe Root. "If we've got guys who can bowl a few overs then it's great. Nice to be able to do that in last few days. It's been nice to get a few runs, a good stepping stone towards the Champions Trophy. The South Africa series will be really good for us to be under some pressure."

That just about wraps things up for today. A gentle start for England to their season. Here's Andrew Miller's report. We'll be back for the series against South Africa, while we will also have coverage of the tri-series from Ireland. For now, though, from Andrew McGlashan and Alan Gardner it's goodbye and thanks for joining us.

flicked from outside off into the leg side
length ball at off stump, 89mph, defended
tries for the yorker, comes out a low full toss which is pushed to cover

headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales b Murtagh 32 (35b 6x4 0x6 46m) SR: 91.42

dismissalComment.html: bowled him, Murtagh strikes! Ireland have their wicket, and it's just reward for some forensic probing from the Middlesex old stager on his home ground... It was on a perfect length, nipping back up the slope, Hales was really in no-man's land trying to drive and the ball snaked between bat and pad to hit middle and leg. That's a bingo!

headshotImage.caption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Roy c Stirling b McCarthy 20 (33b 3x4 0x6 58m) SR: 60.6

dismissalComment.html: full and nailed on the drive - straight to extra cover! Roy falls, wasn't to the pitch and although he flashed hard, it basically went straight into Stirling's hands as he put them up instinctively in front of his face. McCarthy bellows in delight and England have lost both openers

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root c Balbirnie b Chase 73 (73b 8x4 0x6 106m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: skips out and launches the ball... straight to mid-off! Root departs trying to lift the tempo, solid connection on the shot but didn't get enough elevation and he ended up drilling it to the man on the edge of the ring

headshotImage.caption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c Joyce b McCarthy 76 (79b 5x4 2x6 108m) SR: 96.2

dismissalComment.html: strikes first ball, Morgan dinking to extra cover! The change works and again McCarthy gets a wicket in his first over... Like Root, Morgan was looking to get on with things, he made a bit of room but this was well bowled, a cutter giving him less pace to work with and he sliced it to the right of Joyce, who plunged forward to hold a good catch

headshotImage.caption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sam Billings c KJ O'Brien b Dockrell 7 (10b 1x4 0x6 17m) SR: 70

dismissalComment.html: skips down the pitch... but Billings holes out! Wasn't quite the full-blooded mow that shot required to land it in the pavilion - more of a bottom-handed flip that he was looking to hit squarer - and KOB takes a smart running catch to continue Ireland's resurgence

headshotImage.caption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Adil Rashid c NJ O'Brien b Chase 39 (25b 5x4 0x6 34m) SR: 156

dismissalComment.html: short and paddled to leg, kisses the top edge - and O'Brien snaffles it! Think that might have been a slower-ball bouncer and it does for Rashid, but not after a lickety-split 39 from 25 to dash Ireland's hopes of keeping the target below 300

dismissalText.commentary: Ed Joyce b Root 16 (43b 1x4 0x6 64m) SR: 37.2

dismissalComment.html: through him! Root does it again in his first over. Slides a quicker ball down the slope, Joyce was giving himself room as well, he misses playing off the back foot and the leg stump is hit

headshotImage.caption: Jake Ball player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jake Ball player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling c Billings b Ball 48 (42b 8x4 1x6 52m) SR: 114.28

dismissalComment.html: huge appeal for caught behind! Not given by Tim Robinson. England call for the review. Billings (and Ball) are certain. Stirling clashing outside off at a back-of-a-length delivery. There's a spike on Ultra Edge, this will be out

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield b Wood 82 (83b 6x4 1x6 103m) SR: 98.79

dismissalComment.html: and the captain goes! Trying to manufacture something, moving across his crease to scoop Wood towards fine leg (a challenge) and he misses. A fine innings by the Ireland skipper who shows his frustration as he walks off

headshotImage.caption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Andy Balbirnie lbw b Plunkett 2 (8b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: stuck on the crease, struck on the pads... given! Looked a touch leg side but Balbirne elects not to review it, so Plunkett picks up a wicket and Ireland are now three down. He was quite a way back and that is probably what convinced Paul Reiffel

headshotImage.caption: David Willey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: David Willey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Niall O'Brien c Willey b Root 15 (17b 0x4 1x6 16m) SR: 88.23

dismissalComment.html: goes downtown again... but picks out long-on this time! Not out of the middle, maybe darted in a little quicker and O'Brien couldn't get out to it, David Willey had to come in off the rope and clasp it low down

dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson c Hales b Root 13 (24b 1x4 0x6 24m) SR: 54.16

dismissalComment.html: tossed up outside off, Wilson swipes hard - and sends it straight to deep point! Root breaks the stand and pick up his third wicket, forever ruining the symmetry of having a best of 2 for 9 in all three international formats. Gah!

headshotImage.caption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jake Ball player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jake Ball player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kevin O'Brien c Ball b Rashid 18 (10b 0x4 2x6 12m) SR: 180

dismissalComment.html: slogs across the line, big top edge - and goodnight, KOB! Rashid wins the duel, he kept tossing it up and he's rewarded with his first wicket of the day, a rather ungainly hoick from O'Brien and it didn't travel far in the end, taken by the man backpedalling on the edge of the ring at backward square leg

dismissalText.commentary: George Dockrell b Wood 28 (30b 2x4 1x6 56m) SR: 93.33

dismissalComment.html: all over! That's a convincing way to end things as Wood spears a pinpoint yorker through Dockrell
